.TH "p9_virtio_zc_request" 9 "p9_virtio_zc_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
p9_virtio_zc_request \- issue a zero copy request
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" p9_virtio_zc_request
.BI "(struct p9_client *client "  ","
.BI "struct p9_req_t *req "  ","
.BI "struct iov_iter *uidata "  ","
.BI "struct iov_iter *uodata "  ","
.BI "int inlen "  ","
.BI "int outlen "  ","
.BI "int in_hdr_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "client" 12
client instance issuing the request
.IP "req" 12
request to be issued
.IP "uidata" 12
user buffer that should be used for zero copy read
.IP "uodata" 12
user buffer that should be used for zero copy write
.IP "inlen" 12
read buffer size
.IP "outlen" 12
write buffer size
.IP "in_hdr_len" 12
reader header size, This is the size of response protocol data
